---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Winnelo"
  description="The terms governing your use of the Winnelo platform."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-container">

      <div class="legal-header">
        <p class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="legal-title">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="legal-date">Last updated: April 8, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-body">

        <p class="intro">
          Please read these Terms of Service carefully before using Winnelo. By creating an account
          or accessing the platform, you agree to be bound by these terms. If you do not agree,
          you may not use Winnelo.
        </p>

        <section>
          <h2>1. About Winnelo</h2>
          <p>
            Winnelo is a microlearning platform. The platform enables
            organisations to deliver competitive, quiz-based training to their teams. Administrators
            create and publish challenge content; learners complete challenges, earn XP, and compete
            on leaderboards.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By registering for an account, accepting an invitation, or otherwise using Winnelo, you
            confirm that you are at least 16 years old, have the authority to enter into these Terms
            (whether on your own behalf or on behalf of an organisation), and agree to comply with
            all applicable laws.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you are accessing Winnelo on behalf of an organisation, "you" refers to that
            organisation, and you represent that you have authority to bind it to these Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. Accounts</h2>

          <h3>Registration</h3>
          <p>
            To use Winnelo, you must register with a valid email address and create a password. You
            are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your credentials and for all
            activity that occurs under your account.
          </p>

          <h3>Account Types</h3>
          <p>
            Winnelo has two account roles: <strong>Administrators</strong>, who manage the
            organisation, create challenge content, and invite team members; and
            <strong>Learners</strong>, who participate in challenges and appear on leaderboards.
            Your role is set at account creation or by your organisation's administrator.
          </p>

          <h3>Account Security</h3>
          <p>
            You must notify us immediately at
            <a href="mailto:hello@winnelo.com">hello@winnelo.com</a> if you suspect unauthorised
            access to your account. We are not liable for any loss resulting from unauthorised use
            of your credentials.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Use of the Platform</h2>

          <h3>Permitted Use</h3>
          <p>
            You may use Winnelo solely for legitimate internal training and learning purposes within
            your organisation, in accordance with these Terms and all applicable laws.
          </p>

          <h3>Prohibited Conduct</h3>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Use Winnelo for any unlawful purpose or in violation of applicable law</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to the platform or other users' accounts</li>
            <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any part of Winnelo</li>
            <li>Introduce malware, viruses, or any other malicious code</li>
            <li>Scrape or systematically extract data from the platform</li>
            <li>Use automated tools to interact with the platform in a way not sanctioned by Winnelo</li>
            <li>Impersonate any person or entity</li>
            <li>Share your account credentials with others or allow multiple individuals to use a single account</li>
            <li>Use the platform in a way that could damage, disable, or impair its operation</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Administrator Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>
            Administrators are responsible for all content they create or publish on Winnelo. By
            publishing content, you represent that:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>You have the right to use and publish the content</li>
            <li>The content does not infringe the intellectual property rights of any third party</li>
            <li>The content is accurate to the best of your knowledge and does not contain harmful or misleading material</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Administrators are also responsible for managing user access within their organisation,
            including inviting, supervising, and removing learners where necessary.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. AI-Generated Content</h2>
          <p>
            Winnelo offers an AI-assisted question generation feature powered by Anthropic's Claude.
            Content generated by AI is provided as a starting point for administrators and must be
            reviewed before publishing. Winnelo does not guarantee the accuracy, completeness, or
            suitability of AI-generated content. Administrators remain solely responsible for all
            published content.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>

          <h3>Our Platform</h3>
          <p>
            Winnelo, including all software, designs, branding, and underlying technology, is the
            exclusive property of Winnelo and is protected by intellectual property laws. Nothing
            in these Terms grants you any rights beyond what is necessary to use the platform as
            described.
          </p>

          <h3>Your Content</h3>
          <p>
            You retain ownership of any content you create on Winnelo. By publishing content on the
            platform, you grant Winnelo a limited, non-exclusive licence to store, display, and
            deliver that content to the intended recipients within your organisation for the purpose
            of providing the service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Service Availability</h2>
          <p>
            We aim to keep Winnelo available at all times, but we do not guarantee uninterrupted or
            error-free access. We may suspend or modify the platform for maintenance, security
            updates, or other operational reasons, and will endeavour to provide reasonable notice
            of planned downtime where practical.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p>
            Winnelo is provided "as is" and "as available", without warranties of any kind, express
            or implied. To the fullest extent permitted by law, Winnelo disclaims all warranties,
            including implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and
            non-infringement.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Winnelo and its officers, employees,
            and affiliates will not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential,
            or punitive damages arising from or related to your use of Winnelo.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our total aggregate liability for any claims relating to the platform will not exceed
            the greater of (a) the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim, or
            (b) £100 GBP.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Indemnification</h2>
          <p>
            You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Winnelo and its officers, employees, and
            affiliates from any claims, damages, losses, or expenses (including legal fees) arising
            from your use of Winnelo, your violation of these Terms, or your infringement of any
            third-party rights.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>12. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            Either party may terminate use of the platform at any time. We reserve the right to
            suspend or permanently deactivate accounts that violate these Terms, without prior
            notice. Upon termination, your right to access Winnelo ceases immediately.
          </p>
          <p>
            Provisions that by their nature should survive termination — including intellectual
            property rights, disclaimer of warranties, and limitation of liability — will remain
            in effect.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>13. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms from time to time to reflect changes to the platform or legal
            requirements. When we do, we will update the "Last updated" date above and, for material
            changes, notify account holders by email. Continued use of Winnelo after changes are posted
            constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>14. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of England and
            Wales. Any disputes arising from or related to these Terms will be subject to the
            exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>15. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>For questions about these Terms, please contact us:</p>
          <div class="contact-card">
            <p class="contact-label">Winnelo</p>
            <p><a href="mailto:hello@winnelo.com">hello@winnelo.com</a></p>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    flex: 1;
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding: 64px 48px 80px;
  }

  .legal-container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ── Header ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .legal-header {
    padding-bottom: 40px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e4e4e7;
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }

  .legal-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #0047ab;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .legal-title {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 4vw, 48px);
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: #1a1c1c;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .legal-date {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #71717a;
  }

  /* ── Body ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .legal-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 40px;
  }

  .intro {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 26px;
    color: #71717a;
  }

  section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  section h2 {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 15px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2px;
    color: #1a1c1c;
  }

  section h3 {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 1.1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #71717a;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  section p {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 26px;
    color: #3f3f46;
  }

  section ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  section li {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 24px;
    color: #3f3f46;
  }

  section a {
    color: #0047ab;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  section a:hover { color: #003a8c; }

  /* ── Contact card ─────────────────────────────────────── */
  .contact-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #e4e4e7;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .contact-label {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 1.1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #71717a;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ───────────────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .legal-page { padding: 40px 24px 64px; }
  }
</style>
